            <p>1218 N. 12th Street<lb/>
                Philadelphia June 7&#47;87<lb/></p>
            <p>Dear Mr. Morais<lb/></p>
            <p>In reference to your request that I<lb/> should speak in Synagogue next Saturday<lb/> I will say that after some deliberation<lb/> I have decided to accept.  If you think<lb/> that I can say anything worth listening<lb/> to or likely to be of any benefit I<lb/> am willing to try though not without<lb/> some misgivings and considerable reluc&#45;<lb/>tance.  As you are in a measure re&#45;<lb/>sponsible&#44; or will at least be held so&#44;<lb/> for anything said from your pulpit&#44; I<lb/> shall of course submit to you the<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>MS of my remarks&#44; some time during the<lb/> course of the week<lb/> Truly Yours<lb/> Cyrus Adler<lb/></p>
            </body>
    </text>
